1
00:01:03,925 --> 00:01:05,643
Who are you?

2
00:01:05,643 --> 00:01:07,600
Move aside.

3
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:10,343
I'm getting my body back.

4
00:01:33,305 --> 00:01:34,637
Honey.

5
00:01:35,677 --> 00:01:37,063
Honey!

6
00:01:50,197 --> 00:01:52,557
Oh my, Dr. Lee!

7
00:01:54,976 --> 00:01:57,456
Come here, quick!

8
00:01:58,478 --> 00:02:00,236
He was fine earlier.

9
00:02:00,236 --> 00:02:01,406
What did he do?

10
00:02:01,406 --> 00:02:03,506
Do something!

11
00:02:08,590 --> 00:02:13,637
If I get close, do we both die?

12
00:02:16,745 --> 00:02:18,515
That psycho.

13
00:02:18,515 --> 00:02:20,773
Was he trying to headbutt Father?

14
00:02:20,773 --> 00:02:23,314
- I'll handle it.
- I'll do it.

15
00:02:24,745 --> 00:02:26,464
She must be shaken.

16
00:02:26,464 --> 00:02:28,236
Please look after her.

17
00:02:29,277 --> 00:02:31,950
Do you know who I am?

18
00:02:32,714 --> 00:02:36,307
Oh, Chairman Kang! Are you awake?

19
00:02:38,056 --> 00:02:40,482
Move! Step aside!

20
00:02:50,197 --> 00:02:53,325
- You...
- You tipped off the news, huh?

21
00:02:53,325 --> 00:02:55,737
Is it true my dad hit and ran?

22
00:02:55,737 --> 00:02:57,472
Why are you here?

23
00:02:57,472 --> 00:03:00,742
You should be in New York. Why are you here?

24
00:03:01,429 --> 00:03:03,512
You know me?

25
00:03:03,512 --> 00:03:05,213
You work at Choiseong?

26
00:03:05,213 --> 00:03:07,349
Who said you could?

27
00:03:08,316 --> 00:03:11,613
Then who said you could do that to my dad?

28
00:03:11,613 --> 00:03:13,288
You ruined my plan.

29
00:03:13,288 --> 00:03:16,324
- Who the hell are you?
- Let go!

30
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:19,483
I'm your father!

31
00:03:19,483 --> 00:03:21,349
Who the hell are you?

32
00:03:21,349 --> 00:03:25,236
Learned to fight abroad? Let go!

33
00:03:25,236 --> 00:03:26,968
I'm out of time!

34
00:03:26,968 --> 00:03:28,820
Your dad's dying!

35
00:03:31,069 --> 00:03:32,742
My dad is...

36
00:03:33,386 --> 00:03:36,116
- dying?
- Yeah.

37
00:03:36,116 --> 00:03:38,523
Now you're worried, huh?

38
00:03:38,523 --> 00:03:40,520
About my dad?

39
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:42,026
Me?

40
00:03:42,789 --> 00:03:44,493
I'm worried about myself.

41
00:03:44,493 --> 00:03:46,161
I'll lose my shot at revenge.

42
00:03:46,161 --> 00:03:48,416
What?

43
00:03:50,647 --> 00:03:53,424
What happened with my dad?

44
00:03:53,424 --> 00:03:55,424
Tell me!

45
00:03:58,514 --> 00:04:01,582
Sir, I found Hwang Jun Hyeon.

46
00:04:07,543 --> 00:04:09,899
I'm Kang Jae Seong of Choiseong Trading.

47
00:04:09,899 --> 00:04:12,836
Thank God you weren't badly hurt.

48
00:04:12,836 --> 00:04:16,354
This is my sister, CEO Kang Jae Gyeong.

49
00:04:17,152 --> 00:04:22,338
Can we talk about my father's accident?

50
00:04:23,646 --> 00:04:25,392
Sure.

51
00:04:36,798 --> 00:04:40,635
Could Hwang Jun Hyeon be the news tipster?

52
00:04:40,635 --> 00:04:42,792
He just woke up in the ER.

53
00:04:42,792 --> 00:04:44,726
The timing doesn't fit.

54
00:04:47,582 --> 00:04:52,028
You're sure the twins saw Chairman Kang last?

55
00:04:52,028 --> 00:04:53,054
Yes.

56
00:04:53,054 --> 00:04:56,925
He was furious right after seeing them.

57
00:04:57,674 --> 00:04:59,505
"Furious?"

58
00:04:59,505 --> 00:05:04,165
They must've wiped my dashcam footage.

59
00:05:04,165 --> 00:05:06,034
Bring Manager Jang.

60
00:05:06,034 --> 00:05:08,132
Pull every CCTV clip too.

61
00:05:08,132 --> 00:05:09,403
Yes, sir.

62
00:05:12,704 --> 00:05:15,032
Behind the hit-and-run...

63
00:05:15,032 --> 00:05:18,385
My brother and sister were involved.

64
00:05:25,153 --> 00:05:26,575
Mom?

65
00:05:36,331 --> 00:05:40,019
She's my driver. I need her to run an errand.

66
00:05:40,019 --> 00:05:42,045
Thank you.

67
00:05:44,672 --> 00:05:48,343
Wow, such charisma!

68
00:05:49,052 --> 00:05:50,345
Are you crazy?

69
00:05:50,345 --> 00:05:53,575
You came back to Korea
without your dad's permission?

70
00:05:53,575 --> 00:05:56,119
I meant to call.

71
00:05:56,119 --> 00:05:58,987
Are you trying to get killed by your siblings?

72
00:05:58,987 --> 00:06:01,549
You promised to stay away from Choiseong.

73
00:06:02,691 --> 00:06:06,256
You've spent your whole life
bowing to the Kangs.

74
00:06:06,256 --> 00:06:08,360
How long will you keep that up?

75
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:10,544
You're a Kang too.

76
00:06:10,544 --> 00:06:13,634
I'm only a Kang on paper.

77
00:06:13,634 --> 00:06:16,514
Come on, watch your mouth.

78
00:06:21,131 --> 00:06:24,160
How is Dad?

79
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:26,928
He'll wake up soon.

80
00:06:27,983 --> 00:06:29,436
Good.

81
00:06:29,436 --> 00:06:31,451
He can't die yet.

82
00:06:35,590 --> 00:06:37,956
[Was Chairman Kang really driving?]

83
00:06:40,828 --> 00:06:42,303
This is so creepy.

84
00:06:42,303 --> 00:06:45,136
We don't know who was driving yet.

85
00:06:45,136 --> 00:06:47,740
He's strict, but he has a conscience.

86
00:06:47,740 --> 00:06:50,853
No one pays like Choiseong.

87
00:06:50,853 --> 00:06:53,973
So who was really driving?

88
00:06:53,973 --> 00:06:55,690
One of the CEOs, I heard.

89
00:06:55,690 --> 00:06:58,630
I knew it. He's taking the fall.

90
00:06:58,630 --> 00:07:03,567
No way. If not him, why fake a coma?

91
00:07:03,567 --> 00:07:05,186
Honor means everything to him.

92
00:07:05,186 --> 00:07:08,356
Guess he doesn't want jail in his final years.

93
00:07:08,356 --> 00:07:10,176
That can't be true.

94
00:07:10,176 --> 00:07:12,398
Why keep defending him?

95
00:07:12,398 --> 00:07:14,872
Are you his secret daughter?

96
00:07:14,872 --> 00:07:16,101
Look at this.

97
00:07:16,101 --> 00:07:18,667
There's no real proof there either.

98
00:07:18,667 --> 00:07:20,526
It's all just rumors.

99
00:07:29,029 --> 00:07:32,347
We didn't have to leak it ourselves.

100
00:07:32,347 --> 00:07:34,882
What if the news brings out a witness?

101
00:07:34,882 --> 00:07:36,637
It would've come out anyway.

102
00:07:36,637 --> 00:07:38,458
Better we show our hand first.

103
00:07:39,505 --> 00:07:41,806
If they find out I was driving...

104
00:07:41,806 --> 00:07:44,414
What if that punk has another video?

105
00:07:45,306 --> 00:07:48,227
You saw him attack Father.

106
00:07:50,765 --> 00:07:54,903
I wiped his phone clean. No data recovery.

107
00:07:56,904 --> 00:07:59,982
If Father wakes up, we're out for good.

108
00:07:59,982 --> 00:08:03,366
This is our only way out.

109
00:08:03,366 --> 00:08:06,366
Nothing ever sticks to him.

110
00:08:06,366 --> 00:08:09,459
Now we can force him out legally.

111
00:08:10,618 --> 00:08:13,921
You want to stain Father's career?

112
00:08:13,921 --> 00:08:17,392
That's how we break his loyalists.

113
00:08:18,292 --> 00:08:21,363
There's just one man left to handle.

114
00:08:26,910 --> 00:08:29,160
You've been through a lot.

115
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:31,136
Are you feeling okay?

116
00:08:32,769 --> 00:08:35,146
Shouldn't you worry about your father?

117
00:08:35,146 --> 00:08:36,706
He's still in a coma.

118
00:08:36,706 --> 00:08:40,379
He is old. What can we do?

119
00:08:40,379 --> 00:08:44,752
Still, thank God someone tipped off the news.

120
00:08:44,752 --> 00:08:49,747
By any chance, do you have footage

121
00:08:49,747 --> 00:08:51,827
of the driver's face?

122
00:08:51,827 --> 00:08:54,507
We only want to help.

123
00:08:54,507 --> 00:08:56,531
And compensate you.

124
00:08:56,531 --> 00:09:00,034
I'm sorry for my father's terrible crime.

125
00:09:00,034 --> 00:09:02,263
I don't know how to apologize.

126
00:09:05,591 --> 00:09:08,281
He didn't even settle with you?

127
00:09:08,281 --> 00:09:10,534
That's just cruel.

128
00:09:13,681 --> 00:09:15,917
Your father told me.

129
00:09:15,917 --> 00:09:20,985
His own kids stole his car,
crashed it, and ran.

130
00:09:20,985 --> 00:09:22,709
"Terrible crime?"

131
00:09:22,709 --> 00:09:24,175
"You're sorry?"

132
00:09:24,175 --> 00:09:27,538
I know what you did!

133
00:09:27,538 --> 00:09:29,875
Your father's in a coma,

134
00:09:29,875 --> 00:09:33,402
so you leaked that it was his car.

135
00:09:33,402 --> 00:09:36,938
You wanted to pin it all on him?

136
00:09:37,982 --> 00:09:39,641
Shameless.

137
00:09:39,641 --> 00:09:42,876
How dare you make your father a criminal?

138
00:09:43,742 --> 00:09:46,172
After all the messes

139
00:09:46,172 --> 00:09:48,852
I cleaned up for you?

140
00:09:49,884 --> 00:09:52,111
Father said that?

141
00:09:52,111 --> 00:09:53,689
Do you have proof?

142
00:09:54,947 --> 00:09:56,439
Do you?

143
00:09:57,801 --> 00:10:00,425
Proof Kang Yong Ho was driving...

144
00:10:00,425 --> 00:10:02,025
Do you have it?

145
00:10:02,025 --> 00:10:04,154
You wicked brats.

146
00:10:04,154 --> 00:10:06,648
This is why I won't give you Choiseong.

147
00:10:06,648 --> 00:10:10,067
Chairman? Don't even dream of it!

148
00:10:11,842 --> 00:10:13,719
What the hell are you doing?

149
00:10:13,719 --> 00:10:15,566
We're usually gentle.

150
00:10:15,566 --> 00:10:18,613
But you only believe his lies.

151
00:10:18,613 --> 00:10:20,815
That's who our father is.

152
00:10:20,815 --> 00:10:22,900
He causes trouble,

153
00:10:22,900 --> 00:10:25,022
then pins it on his kids.

154
00:10:26,387 --> 00:10:27,842
Your career is over, huh?

155
00:10:27,842 --> 00:10:30,091
Take the settlement money.

156
00:10:30,091 --> 00:10:32,943
We'll give you whatever you want.

157
00:10:32,943 --> 00:10:34,930
To me, an apology is money.

158
00:10:34,930 --> 00:10:38,926
Nothing says sorry like paying what it's worth.

159
00:10:39,607 --> 00:10:42,273
Write ten billion won if you want.

160
00:10:45,106 --> 00:10:47,048
So think carefully,

161
00:10:47,048 --> 00:10:48,641
Mr. Hwang.

162
00:10:50,577 --> 00:10:53,708
Until he answers, don't let him out.

163
00:10:53,708 --> 00:10:54,801
Got it.

164
00:10:57,547 --> 00:10:59,191
Ma'am...

165
00:10:59,820 --> 00:11:01,188
Hit-and-run crime!

166
00:11:01,188 --> 00:11:03,651
We're outside Choiseong Group HQ.

167
00:11:03,651 --> 00:11:07,328
Chairman Kang has not regained consciousness.

168
00:11:07,328 --> 00:11:10,636
Unverified rumors now claim

169
00:11:10,636 --> 00:11:15,903
CEO Kang Jae Gyeong
or Kang Jae Seong was driving.

170
00:11:15,903 --> 00:11:17,453
What's going on?

171
00:11:17,453 --> 00:11:19,719
After these allegations,

172
00:11:19,719 --> 00:11:22,428
Choiseong Group's stock plunged today.

173
00:11:22,428 --> 00:11:24,801
This has investors on edge.

174
00:11:24,801 --> 00:11:29,307
Shareholders and investors
are protesting outside HQ.

175
00:11:30,918 --> 00:11:32,524
Explain yourselves!

176
00:11:36,605 --> 00:11:38,388
Is Chairman Kang awake?

177
00:11:38,388 --> 00:11:41,915
Choiseong stock crashed today.
When will you respond?

178
00:11:41,915 --> 00:11:43,405
Have you met the victim?

179
00:11:43,405 --> 00:11:44,999
Did he say Chairman Kang did it?

180
00:11:44,999 --> 00:11:48,293
Some say one of you may have been driving.

181
00:11:48,293 --> 00:11:51,707
Chairman Kang covered up all your scandals,
right?

182
00:11:51,707 --> 00:11:56,287
Your draft exemption, your fake degrees,
your kids' birth tourism,

183
00:11:56,287 --> 00:11:59,823
and your 50-billion-won
overseas property schemes.

184
00:11:59,823 --> 00:12:01,408
What the hell are you saying?

185
00:12:01,408 --> 00:12:03,099
That was all...

186
00:12:03,099 --> 00:12:05,717
done on our father's orders.

187
00:12:05,717 --> 00:12:07,503
We were...

188
00:12:07,503 --> 00:12:11,603
never in a place to say no.

189
00:12:12,590 --> 00:12:15,400
We're just powerless kids.

190
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:16,899
Sorry.

191
00:12:24,183 --> 00:12:25,806
Are you insane?

192
00:12:25,806 --> 00:12:29,805
Father could wake up and send us to jail.

193
00:12:30,471 --> 00:12:32,782
Then we don't let him wake up.

194
00:12:34,878 --> 00:12:38,615
Why do you think
I moved Father to his hospital?

195
00:12:38,615 --> 00:12:40,040
He...

196
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:42,731
has never said no to me.

197
00:12:43,562 --> 00:12:45,715
Heaven is on our side.

198
00:12:47,895 --> 00:12:50,031
What about Manager Jang?

199
00:12:50,031 --> 00:12:52,129
Secretary Nam handled him.

200
00:12:53,388 --> 00:12:56,246
The police are covered too.

201
00:12:57,055 --> 00:12:59,819
As long as that punk keeps quiet,

202
00:12:59,819 --> 00:13:01,543
no one will know.

203
00:13:49,511 --> 00:13:51,022
You little brats.

204
00:13:51,022 --> 00:13:53,935
I built this villa.

205
00:14:17,456 --> 00:14:20,766
A photo from the hit-and-run scene on the 27th

206
00:14:20,766 --> 00:14:23,725
showed this car, sparking controversy.

207
00:14:23,725 --> 00:14:28,028
A witness says Chairman Kang
wanted it fixed right away.

208
00:14:28,028 --> 00:14:29,840
You knew, then.

209
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:35,707
He said he hit a guardrail dodging a cat.
So I just fixed it.

210
00:14:35,707 --> 00:14:37,731
You didn't find that strange?

211
00:14:37,731 --> 00:14:40,208
How could I question him?

212
00:14:40,208 --> 00:14:42,173
Those little...

213
00:14:42,173 --> 00:14:43,384
Driver,

214
00:14:43,384 --> 00:14:44,846
hurry!

215
00:14:44,846 --> 00:14:47,340
Was the repair rushed?

216
00:14:47,340 --> 00:14:49,706
I said hurry!

217
00:15:02,364 --> 00:15:05,199
- Arrest Kang Yong Ho!
- Arrest him!

218
00:15:05,199 --> 00:15:07,969
- Get him out!
- Get him out!

219
00:15:11,472 --> 00:15:12,773
[No Criminal CEO]

220
00:15:12,773 --> 00:15:13,992
[Don't Cover Up] [Compensate!]

221
00:15:17,812 --> 00:15:18,880
[Criminal]

222
00:15:22,582 --> 00:15:23,629
[Hit-and-Run CEO Out]

223
00:15:37,732 --> 00:15:42,071
[Sinful Choiseong! Arrest Kang Yong Ho!]

224
00:15:48,154 --> 00:15:53,018
Chairman Kang once saved
Choiseong from every crisis.

225
00:15:53,018 --> 00:15:55,162
Now he's the center of public outrage.

226
00:15:55,162 --> 00:15:57,543
Choiseong stock has plunged...

227
00:15:57,543 --> 00:15:59,487
Kang Yong Ho's decades-long reign...

228
00:15:59,487 --> 00:16:02,223
Analysts say this could shake
Choiseong's power structure...

229
00:16:02,223 --> 00:16:06,728
- A crisis for...
- This may become a crisis for Choiseong.

230
00:16:06,728 --> 00:16:09,681
He's really lost his mind.

231
00:16:09,681 --> 00:16:12,946
I know. Why cause trouble at his age...

232
00:16:12,946 --> 00:16:16,323
Maybe that's why he gave up the chair.

233
00:16:16,323 --> 00:16:18,233
Will Choiseong go under?

234
00:16:18,233 --> 00:16:20,287
He's rich. Why not settle?

235
00:16:20,287 --> 00:16:21,607
So embarrassing.

236
00:16:21,607 --> 00:16:23,411
What do we do now?

237
00:16:23,411 --> 00:16:26,457
Now coming to work feels shameful.

238
00:16:26,457 --> 00:16:28,147
Choiseong fell this low?

239
00:16:28,147 --> 00:16:31,268
People keep asking if the hit-and-run is true.

240
00:16:31,268 --> 00:16:35,114
You think my Choiseong will fall that easily?

241
00:16:47,121 --> 00:16:49,358
How dare you...

242
00:16:49,358 --> 00:16:54,005
I gave my life to build Choiseong.

243
00:16:54,005 --> 00:16:57,205
And you crushed it like this?

244
00:16:57,205 --> 00:16:58,706
But...

245
00:17:03,568 --> 00:17:06,007
I can't go back.

246
00:17:06,988 --> 00:17:09,644
What can I do in this body?

247
00:17:23,304 --> 00:17:25,667
[Chairman Kang Yong Ho]

248
00:17:25,667 --> 00:17:27,824
Public opinion is at rock bottom.

249
00:17:27,824 --> 00:17:31,890
Father must admit guilt and apologize now.

250
00:17:31,890 --> 00:17:33,548
Let's not rush.

251
00:17:33,548 --> 00:17:35,947
Until we get clearer evidence...

252
00:17:35,947 --> 00:17:38,634
His car was caught on camera.

253
00:17:38,634 --> 00:17:42,504
All the evidence points to him.

254
00:17:42,504 --> 00:17:45,354
You know how fast a group's image can fall.

255
00:17:45,354 --> 00:17:48,363
Right now, saving Choiseong comes first.

256
00:17:52,734 --> 00:17:54,471
Father asked

257
00:17:54,471 --> 00:17:59,954
us to protect the company
before the board meeting.

258
00:18:05,007 --> 00:18:07,234
I heard no such thing.

259
00:18:07,234 --> 00:18:11,451
Does my father report everything to you?

260
00:18:11,451 --> 00:18:12,821
He praised you a little,

261
00:18:12,821 --> 00:18:15,475
and now you think you outrank us?

262
00:18:18,934 --> 00:18:21,751
His image has hit rock bottom.

263
00:18:21,751 --> 00:18:26,637
It seems impossible for him
to keep his position now.

264
00:18:31,697 --> 00:18:35,575
So what do you suggest?

265
00:18:35,575 --> 00:18:37,368
CEOs?

266
00:18:40,328 --> 00:18:42,645
You should announce it yourself.

267
00:18:42,645 --> 00:18:46,265
The board will remove him as chairman.

268
00:18:46,265 --> 00:18:48,160
No, hold on.

269
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:49,775
That's too...

270
00:18:51,191 --> 00:18:52,995
- Ma'am, at the press...
- Good.

271
00:18:52,995 --> 00:18:55,448
- Get the press conference ready.
- No...

272
00:18:55,448 --> 00:18:57,247
Hwang Jun Hyeon is there.

273
00:19:02,470 --> 00:19:06,463
[Choiseong Group Emergency Press Conference]

274
00:19:21,768 --> 00:19:25,065
Everyone's already here.

275
00:19:25,065 --> 00:19:28,095
How did you get in here?

276
00:19:28,095 --> 00:19:30,279
We still need to talk.

277
00:19:30,279 --> 00:19:31,817
Let's talk...

278
00:19:36,338 --> 00:19:38,043
I, Kang...

279
00:19:42,191 --> 00:19:44,410
I, Hwang Jun Hyeon,

280
00:19:45,121 --> 00:19:48,160
am here to reveal the truth.

281
00:19:49,650 --> 00:19:52,889
The hit-and-run driver who ran me over was...

282
00:19:52,889 --> 00:19:54,621
Wait, Mr. Hwang!

283
00:19:54,621 --> 00:19:57,138
Chairman Kang Yong Ho.

284
00:20:08,847 --> 00:20:10,317
Who?

285
00:20:13,348 --> 00:20:15,130
I saw him...

286
00:20:18,078 --> 00:20:19,935
with my own eyes.

287
00:20:25,628 --> 00:20:27,903
Chairman Kang Yong Ho is...

288
00:20:33,501 --> 00:20:35,536
the real culprit.

289
00:20:36,258 --> 00:20:38,583
So he alone should be punished.

290
00:20:42,514 --> 00:20:44,117
So...

291
00:20:47,509 --> 00:20:49,280
Those two...

292
00:20:51,719 --> 00:20:53,610
and Choiseong...

293
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:01,813
did nothing wrong.

294
00:21:22,669 --> 00:21:25,180
He was alone when Father died.

295
00:21:25,180 --> 00:21:27,698
He's lying. The will was forged!

296
00:21:27,698 --> 00:21:30,067
- What's he doing?
- Oh gosh.

297
00:21:32,486 --> 00:21:35,471
How can he lead a group in that body?

298
00:21:35,471 --> 00:21:39,494
He got hurt on-site,
then begged Father for the chair.

299
00:21:42,991 --> 00:21:44,255
How embarrassing.

300
00:21:44,255 --> 00:21:46,217
Take him to a hospital.

301
00:21:47,367 --> 00:21:50,465
Can we trust Choiseong to someone so weak,

302
00:21:50,465 --> 00:21:53,018
living off pity?

303
00:21:59,793 --> 00:22:02,330
But they said

304
00:22:02,330 --> 00:22:05,184
he'd never walk again after the accident.

305
00:22:10,445 --> 00:22:12,941
Choiseong's lights

306
00:22:12,941 --> 00:22:16,352
will never go out.

307
00:22:16,352 --> 00:22:18,523
I will honor Father's will

308
00:22:18,523 --> 00:22:23,345
and make Choiseong
one of Korea's top ten companies.

309
00:22:24,949 --> 00:22:27,615
I will make it happen.

310
00:22:31,827 --> 00:22:34,498
To protect Choiseong,

311
00:22:34,498 --> 00:22:39,138
I'd give myself up a hundred times.

312
00:22:53,389 --> 00:22:55,636
In Choiseong's name,

313
00:22:55,636 --> 00:22:57,889
we promise full compensation.

314
00:22:57,889 --> 00:23:00,176
We are truly sorry.

315
00:23:02,976 --> 00:23:05,527
Choiseong will fully support

316
00:23:05,527 --> 00:23:08,899
Mr. Hwang Jun Hyeon's new life.

317
00:23:08,899 --> 00:23:11,098
Once again, we apologize.

318
00:23:19,059 --> 00:23:21,810
Enjoy your relief.

319
00:23:21,810 --> 00:23:24,302
This isn't over.

320
00:23:25,305 --> 00:23:28,511
Mr. Hwang! One more comment, please!

321
00:23:33,727 --> 00:23:35,021
She's...

322
00:23:40,814 --> 00:23:43,794
Where did he go?

323
00:23:43,794 --> 00:23:45,084
Bang Geul?

324
00:23:46,374 --> 00:23:47,992
Kang Bang Geul.

325
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:55,250
Long time no see, sir.

326
00:23:56,992 --> 00:23:58,746
What are you doing here?

327
00:23:58,746 --> 00:23:59,787
[Intern ID]

328
00:23:59,787 --> 00:24:01,507
A Choiseong intern?

329
00:24:01,507 --> 00:24:04,578
I'll tell you when the time comes.

330
00:24:04,578 --> 00:24:07,195
Until then, keep it from my siblings.

331
00:24:07,195 --> 00:24:09,505
- What?
- You...

332
00:24:09,505 --> 00:24:12,229
You owe me, remember?

333
00:24:17,576 --> 00:24:18,842
[Mommy]

334
00:24:22,256 --> 00:24:24,362
Are you still at the hospital?

335
00:24:25,663 --> 00:24:27,620
That kid...

336
00:24:29,736 --> 00:24:33,416
She has the chairman's eyes.

337
00:25:03,098 --> 00:25:04,704
[Aejeong-ro 307]

338
00:25:33,392 --> 00:25:34,643
What the...

339
00:25:35,825 --> 00:25:37,531
[Resident ID]
[Hwang Jun Hyeon]

340
00:26:18,707 --> 00:26:20,500
Is this thing working?

341
00:26:24,351 --> 00:26:25,757
[Let's go, Choiseong FC!]

342
00:26:45,834 --> 00:26:47,228
[My success makes Grandma smile]

343
00:27:34,349 --> 00:27:36,283
No!

344
00:27:36,283 --> 00:27:38,487
I can't last a second in there!

345
00:27:41,683 --> 00:27:43,849
Why am I so fast?

346
00:27:45,970 --> 00:27:47,893
I forgot...

347
00:27:47,893 --> 00:27:50,874
What it feels like to run like this!

348
00:27:50,874 --> 00:27:55,103
Every nerve's buzzing, alive!

349
00:27:55,103 --> 00:27:56,430
Be careful!

350
00:28:01,504 --> 00:28:03,478
Thank you.

351
00:28:03,478 --> 00:28:04,977
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

352
00:28:05,683 --> 00:28:07,341
Wow.

353
00:28:07,341 --> 00:28:09,695
Guess I've got Sonny speed.

354
00:28:11,019 --> 00:28:14,385
No matter what, I'm never living there!

355
00:28:24,266 --> 00:28:25,566
My cane...

356
00:28:27,834 --> 00:28:29,497
Is he insane?

357
00:28:29,497 --> 00:28:31,607
He called us the culprits.

358
00:28:31,607 --> 00:28:33,897
You know, he escaped the villa.

359
00:28:33,897 --> 00:28:35,607
He's no ordinary guy.

360
00:28:35,607 --> 00:28:37,940
I told my secretary to bring him in.

361
00:28:37,940 --> 00:28:40,425
Did your husband handle Father?

362
00:28:55,927 --> 00:28:57,925
Why are you still here?

363
00:28:57,925 --> 00:29:01,077
After all that happened, I got worried.

364
00:29:02,203 --> 00:29:04,815
He's much calmer now.

365
00:29:04,815 --> 00:29:07,728
He should wake up soon, right?

366
00:29:07,728 --> 00:29:09,224
Don't worry.

367
00:29:09,224 --> 00:29:11,613
You should go home for tonight.

368
00:29:11,613 --> 00:29:14,153
I can't leave him alone.

369
00:29:16,971 --> 00:29:18,420
This is a VIP ward.

370
00:29:18,420 --> 00:29:20,155
You don't need to worry.

371
00:29:20,155 --> 00:29:21,908
You can come later.

372
00:29:21,908 --> 00:29:23,036
Let's go.

373
00:29:33,055 --> 00:29:35,585
I'm taking her home.

374
00:29:35,585 --> 00:29:38,255
I left the shot in the drawer.

375
00:30:43,317 --> 00:30:46,494
She's never been any help.

376
00:30:46,494 --> 00:30:49,311
Do we have to do this ourselves?

377
00:30:49,311 --> 00:30:51,611
It's all for Father.

378
00:30:51,611 --> 00:30:54,881
He worked too hard all his life.

379
00:30:54,881 --> 00:30:56,726
Poor man.

380
00:30:57,794 --> 00:30:59,970
Sleeping so peacefully.

381
00:30:59,970 --> 00:31:01,737
Amazing.

382
00:31:01,737 --> 00:31:05,191
You're scary. Like you planned this...

383
00:31:05,191 --> 00:31:08,720
You sent the guards away
and turned off the CCTV.

384
00:31:10,196 --> 00:31:12,013
This is for you too.

385
00:31:12,013 --> 00:31:14,200
Watch him.

386
00:31:14,200 --> 00:31:15,870
See if he wakes up.

387
00:31:16,673 --> 00:31:19,410
Don't they have a strong sedative?

388
00:31:19,410 --> 00:31:22,588
There's no way he'll wake up already...

389
00:31:24,818 --> 00:31:26,791
He's awake!

390
00:31:28,326 --> 00:31:30,049
Father...

391
00:31:43,697 --> 00:31:44,981
Please...

392
00:31:44,981 --> 00:31:46,623
Oh gosh.

393
00:32:08,290 --> 00:32:09,910
What are you doing?

394
00:33:14,389 --> 00:33:16,291
You okay?

395
00:33:16,291 --> 00:33:17,796
Hwang Jun Hyeon!

396
00:33:18,870 --> 00:33:20,996
Wake up!

397
00:33:20,996 --> 00:33:22,906
Say something!

398
00:33:52,190 --> 00:33:53,461
Dad?

399
00:33:54,883 --> 00:33:56,258
Dad!

400
00:34:37,698 --> 00:34:39,484
I shouldn't have seen it.

401
00:34:40,875 --> 00:34:43,367
I wish I never knew.

402
00:35:00,273 --> 00:35:03,672
It looks like hypoxic brain damage.

403
00:35:04,897 --> 00:35:08,231
But you said he was fine.

404
00:35:08,231 --> 00:35:10,919
He suddenly went into cardiac arrest.

405
00:35:10,919 --> 00:35:12,932
We still need to find the cause.

406
00:35:12,932 --> 00:35:15,995
But his condition is very serious.

407
00:35:15,995 --> 00:35:19,845
You should prepare for the worst.

408
00:35:20,743 --> 00:35:22,228
Ma'am!

409
00:35:40,255 --> 00:35:43,369
I don't think he'll last long.

410
00:35:46,281 --> 00:35:48,821
I'll set up a meeting soon.

411
00:35:49,621 --> 00:35:52,225
It's time to repot.

412
00:35:52,225 --> 00:35:55,501
And I have the perfect pot.

413
00:35:56,885 --> 00:35:59,685
You've waited a long time. Congrats.

414
00:36:07,345 --> 00:36:09,961
So this is how

415
00:36:09,961 --> 00:36:12,787
the great Kang Yong Ho falls.

416
00:36:51,471 --> 00:36:54,108
[Cashier's Check]

417
00:36:57,929 --> 00:36:59,515
I'm curious too.

418
00:36:59,515 --> 00:37:03,852
How much will you want for your precious life?

419
00:37:03,852 --> 00:37:06,609
You don't get to decide my future.

420
00:37:06,609 --> 00:37:11,020
Who are you to say
I won't be Messi or Son Heung Min?

421
00:37:15,776 --> 00:37:18,387
Soccer was everything to me too.

422
00:37:20,614 --> 00:37:22,926
More than Choiseong is to you.

423
00:37:26,839 --> 00:37:29,804
[Give me Choiseong]

424
00:37:32,854 --> 00:37:35,957
I've never written a bad check.

425
00:37:36,807 --> 00:37:38,372
I will...

426
00:37:40,880 --> 00:37:43,169
make it up to you properly.

427
00:37:56,701 --> 00:37:58,712
Why are you here at this hour?

428
00:37:58,712 --> 00:38:00,405
Why so surprised?

429
00:38:00,405 --> 00:38:03,534
We've been looking for you.

430
00:38:03,534 --> 00:38:05,374
Good.

431
00:38:05,374 --> 00:38:08,405
Let's finish our settlement talk.

432
00:38:08,405 --> 00:38:09,671
Say it.

433
00:38:09,671 --> 00:38:12,317
Whatever you want, we'll give it to you.

434
00:38:12,317 --> 00:38:14,472
So please, let's end this.

435
00:38:16,824 --> 00:38:19,165
What I want is...

436
00:38:46,809 --> 00:38:50,586
We're happy to have you
join Choiseong's future.

437
00:38:50,586 --> 00:38:53,919
Let's do great things together, Mr. Hwang.

438
00:38:58,291 --> 00:39:00,391
I won't forget...

439
00:39:02,080 --> 00:39:04,228
this kindness.

440
00:39:10,756 --> 00:39:13,213
Let's take a photo.

441
00:39:13,213 --> 00:39:15,602
Yeah, great.

442
00:39:15,602 --> 00:39:18,427
I'm Hwang Jun Hyeon, Choiseong Group intern.

443
00:39:18,427 --> 00:39:21,355
I look forward to working with you!

444
00:39:26,065 --> 00:39:28,129
What the fuck!

445
00:39:28,129 --> 00:39:30,449
[Hit-and-Run Victim Hwang
Becomes Choiseong Intern]

446
00:39:39,574 --> 00:39:41,980
[Chairman Kang Yong Ho]

447
00:40:13,916 --> 00:40:16,494
Lee Sang Jae,

448
00:40:16,494 --> 00:40:19,285
I should have had you as my own.

449
00:40:21,114 --> 00:40:23,377
Sang Jae.

450
00:40:23,377 --> 00:40:25,771
I missed you.

451
00:40:25,771 --> 00:40:28,117
Why did you really come to Choiseong?

452
00:40:29,638 --> 00:40:31,055
I know.

453
00:40:31,055 --> 00:40:33,581
I know I look suspicious.

454
00:40:33,581 --> 00:40:35,499
But, Sir...

455
00:40:35,499 --> 00:40:37,973
You'll accept me soon.

456
00:40:39,068 --> 00:40:40,123
Accept what?

457
00:40:40,123 --> 00:40:42,925
That I'm the only one here

458
00:40:42,925 --> 00:40:46,449
who cares about Chairman Kang
as much as you do.

459
00:40:46,449 --> 00:40:49,675
So stop looking at me like that.

460
00:40:50,528 --> 00:40:52,560
And please wait a little.

461
00:40:57,211 --> 00:40:59,747
I'll come to you soon.

462
00:41:01,331 --> 00:41:02,366
Why would you...

463
00:41:02,366 --> 00:41:05,047
Because you'll help me do what I need to do.

464
00:41:05,047 --> 00:41:07,208
And what is that?

465
00:41:07,208 --> 00:41:09,714
Protecting Choiseong Group.

466
00:41:12,956 --> 00:41:17,473
Pretty arrogant for a connected intern.

467
00:41:17,473 --> 00:41:19,372
It's my first job.

468
00:41:21,146 --> 00:41:23,563
Your first job

469
00:41:23,563 --> 00:41:26,112
is like your first love.

470
00:41:26,112 --> 00:41:27,151
What?

471
00:41:27,151 --> 00:41:29,974
Like your first love...

472
00:41:30,986 --> 00:41:34,216
A company you never forget.

473
00:41:34,216 --> 00:41:36,573
Even after you leave,

474
00:41:36,573 --> 00:41:40,446
you still call it home.

475
00:41:41,356 --> 00:41:44,082
I hope Choiseong is that place for you.

476
00:41:45,463 --> 00:41:47,463
Chairman...

477
00:41:48,570 --> 00:41:50,618
Sir,

478
00:41:50,618 --> 00:41:53,393
where's Trading Materials Team?

479
00:41:53,393 --> 00:41:56,377
Why us, of all teams?

480
00:41:56,377 --> 00:42:00,574
Everyone thinks our team has no power
and no real value.

481
00:42:00,574 --> 00:42:02,535
Why dump him on us?

482
00:42:02,535 --> 00:42:05,721
He only played soccer. What can he even do?

483
00:42:05,721 --> 00:42:07,286
I know.

484
00:42:07,286 --> 00:42:09,604
Hey, watch your mouth.

485
00:42:09,604 --> 00:42:13,398
He's the chairman's accident victim.

486
00:42:13,398 --> 00:42:14,882
You know...

487
00:42:14,882 --> 00:42:17,875
This came straight from the CEOs.

488
00:42:17,875 --> 00:42:20,355
Take good care of him.

489
00:42:26,474 --> 00:42:29,361
Hey, listen up!

490
00:42:31,145 --> 00:42:34,782
Anyway, don't look at him weird.

491
00:42:34,782 --> 00:42:37,000
Don't leave him out.

492
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:38,518
Especially at lunch.

493
00:42:38,518 --> 00:42:41,824
Take him with you for coffee too.

494
00:42:43,509 --> 00:42:45,169
Yes, sir.

495
00:42:45,169 --> 00:42:47,760
So who'll take him?

496
00:42:47,760 --> 00:42:49,130
Who wants him?

497
00:42:49,130 --> 00:42:51,363
- Well...
- I'm busy with...

498
00:42:51,363 --> 00:42:52,467
Me!

499
00:42:54,862 --> 00:42:56,375
I'll do it.

500
00:42:58,075 --> 00:42:59,540
Bang Geul?

501
00:42:59,540 --> 00:43:00,817
Are you sure?

502
00:43:00,817 --> 00:43:03,492
Your intern PT is coming up.

503
00:43:03,492 --> 00:43:06,346
Team spirit, right? I've got this.

504
00:43:07,106 --> 00:43:08,554
Right.

505
00:43:08,554 --> 00:43:10,983
No one's better for the job.

506
00:43:10,983 --> 00:43:12,818
We're counting on you.

507
00:43:12,818 --> 00:43:13,917
Yes!

508
00:43:26,332 --> 00:43:28,800
Is this the Materials Team 2?

509
00:43:33,572 --> 00:43:36,757
Oh, Mr. Hwang Jun Hyeon.

510
00:43:36,757 --> 00:43:39,641
Welcome, nice to meet you.

511
00:43:39,641 --> 00:43:43,518
You're tall and handsome.

512
00:43:43,518 --> 00:43:44,818
Smile.

513
00:43:47,378 --> 00:43:50,823
What are your main projects?

514
00:43:50,823 --> 00:43:53,345
Are you supporting Yuncheon's SOC project?

515
00:43:53,345 --> 00:43:57,582
You pushed that cost-cutting
logistics upgrade last year.

516
00:43:57,582 --> 00:43:59,264
Is it done?

517
00:44:11,291 --> 00:44:13,768
I'll start his OJT.

518
00:44:13,768 --> 00:44:15,546
Come this way.

519
00:44:21,121 --> 00:44:23,511
Wow, that nutjob...

520
00:44:23,511 --> 00:44:26,977
We really stepped in it, sir.

521
00:44:29,197 --> 00:44:31,564
Help me take this scarf off.

522
00:44:31,564 --> 00:44:32,874
You must be hot.

523
00:44:32,874 --> 00:44:34,739
Hey, let go!

524
00:44:37,287 --> 00:44:39,641
Hello.

525
00:44:39,641 --> 00:44:44,164
Act like an intern. Bow properly first.

526
00:44:44,164 --> 00:44:45,513
Why ask about our projects?

527
00:44:45,513 --> 00:44:48,474
You think you're the chairman?

528
00:44:51,684 --> 00:44:54,222
Ever heard of ownership?

529
00:45:00,524 --> 00:45:02,628
What does an intern do?

530
00:45:02,628 --> 00:45:03,732
[Inventory Status Report]

531
00:45:08,203 --> 00:45:11,239
You don't know Excel?

532
00:45:11,239 --> 00:45:13,771
I do.

533
00:45:13,771 --> 00:45:15,257
I can read it.

534
00:45:16,628 --> 00:45:19,471
Then how did you get into Choiseong?

535
00:45:19,471 --> 00:45:20,615
Forget it.

536
00:45:20,615 --> 00:45:24,180
Make your intranet ID first.
You need to prep for your PT.

537
00:45:24,180 --> 00:45:26,221
You know what a PT is, huh?

538
00:45:26,221 --> 00:45:28,672
Don't treat me like an idiot.

539
00:45:28,672 --> 00:45:31,865
I'll handle it. Stay out of it.

540
00:45:32,852 --> 00:45:36,335
Connected interns don't need PTs to get hired?

541
00:45:36,335 --> 00:45:38,841
You're the chairman's daughter...

542
00:45:41,253 --> 00:45:42,910
Stairs again?

543
00:45:42,910 --> 00:45:45,147
I don't know what you heard,

544
00:45:45,147 --> 00:45:49,010
but if you run your mouth about me again...

545
00:45:49,010 --> 00:45:51,933
You were cute as a kid. But now...

546
00:45:51,933 --> 00:45:53,688
There you go again.

547
00:45:53,688 --> 00:45:55,290
Acting like you know me.

548
00:45:56,977 --> 00:45:59,552
Don't tell anyone I'm his daughter.

549
00:45:59,552 --> 00:46:02,547
And don't say my real name.

550
00:46:02,547 --> 00:46:04,473
I'm Casey. Got it?

551
00:46:06,227 --> 00:46:10,298
Don't disgrace your father. Quit quietly.

552
00:46:10,298 --> 00:46:13,511
You spent all your time clubbing in New York.

553
00:46:14,466 --> 00:46:16,757
Did my brother tell you I was in New York?

554
00:46:16,757 --> 00:46:18,716
How do you know about the clubs?

555
00:46:18,716 --> 00:46:20,542
What are you to the CEOs?

556
00:46:20,542 --> 00:46:22,877
What did you do to my dad...

557
00:46:30,465 --> 00:46:31,830
Dad!

558
00:46:35,285 --> 00:46:37,378
What are you thinking?

559
00:46:37,378 --> 00:46:38,994
Are you done?

560
00:46:42,282 --> 00:46:45,749
Don't act close to me, Kang Bang Geul.

561
00:46:54,020 --> 00:46:55,540
Stay calm.

562
00:46:56,594 --> 00:46:59,394
Wait for solid proof.

563
00:47:00,988 --> 00:47:02,495
Stay calm.

564
00:47:11,615 --> 00:47:14,042
So, Casey Kang...

565
00:47:14,712 --> 00:47:17,761
Is she any good?

566
00:47:20,334 --> 00:47:21,569
Was that for me?

567
00:47:26,344 --> 00:47:28,381
I guess it was.

568
00:47:31,365 --> 00:47:34,897
Must be the accident. He's too casual.

569
00:47:36,672 --> 00:47:38,222
Well, I get it.

570
00:47:38,222 --> 00:47:41,671
Anyway, about our Casey...

571
00:47:42,675 --> 00:47:43,792
Hello.

572
00:47:43,792 --> 00:47:48,422
I'm Casey Kang, a proactive applicant
for Choiseong Trading.

573
00:47:48,422 --> 00:47:50,185
I'll do my best!

574
00:47:50,185 --> 00:47:51,897
She barely passed the aptitude test.

575
00:47:51,897 --> 00:47:55,565
But six languages saved her interview.

576
00:47:55,565 --> 00:47:57,469
Can someone copy the files?

577
00:47:57,469 --> 00:47:59,033
Me! I'll do it.

578
00:47:59,033 --> 00:48:01,390
- Who can book the meeting room?
- Me!

579
00:48:01,390 --> 00:48:02,510
I'll do it.

580
00:48:02,510 --> 00:48:04,307
There's a parcel in the lobby...

581
00:48:04,307 --> 00:48:06,123
Me!

582
00:48:06,123 --> 00:48:07,154
I'll go!

583
00:48:07,154 --> 00:48:09,697
That's why we call her "Yes Kang."

584
00:48:12,758 --> 00:48:15,215
She copies fast and perfectly.

585
00:48:15,215 --> 00:48:17,295
So "Copy Kang."

586
00:48:17,295 --> 00:48:19,352
- Coffee delivery.
- Thank you.

587
00:48:19,352 --> 00:48:22,427
She knew everyone's coffee order.

588
00:48:22,427 --> 00:48:23,759
Coffee delivery.

589
00:48:23,759 --> 00:48:25,831
So "Coffee Kang."

590
00:48:25,831 --> 00:48:26,884
Thank you.

591
00:48:26,884 --> 00:48:30,226
Wait, what team are you from?

592
00:48:30,226 --> 00:48:33,020
Casey Kang from Materials Team 2.

593
00:48:33,020 --> 00:48:34,653
Oh, I see.

594
00:48:34,653 --> 00:48:36,586
But this is a Sales Team dinner.

595
00:48:38,510 --> 00:48:41,447
I'm here to make somaek.

596
00:48:41,447 --> 00:48:42,784
Wait.

597
00:48:42,784 --> 00:48:44,911
Why was she even at another team's dinner?

598
00:48:44,911 --> 00:48:47,233
She went to every team dinner.

599
00:48:47,233 --> 00:48:50,938
Word spread that she made amazing somaek.
"Somaek Kang."

600
00:48:50,938 --> 00:48:52,902
"Foodie Kang" for lunch spots...

601
00:48:52,902 --> 00:48:55,063
"Overtime Kang" for helping seniors.

602
00:48:55,063 --> 00:48:59,619
She's close with the guards
and the cleaning staff too.

603
00:48:59,619 --> 00:49:01,214
"Social Kang."

604
00:49:01,214 --> 00:49:02,534
What a joke.

605
00:49:02,534 --> 00:49:06,393
She's strong, sweet, and capable.

606
00:49:06,393 --> 00:49:09,511
So you should try to be like her...

607
00:49:09,511 --> 00:49:11,641
Is an intern a slave?

608
00:49:12,454 --> 00:49:15,881
How dare you treat
someone's precious daughter like that?

609
00:49:15,881 --> 00:49:18,363
This company's a total mess.

610
00:49:18,363 --> 00:49:20,563
A complete mess!

611
00:49:25,724 --> 00:49:28,196
Oh my gosh!

612
00:49:28,196 --> 00:49:29,928
Get some tissues!

613
00:49:29,928 --> 00:49:31,476
You okay?

614
00:49:31,476 --> 00:49:32,582
Oh my.

615
00:49:35,027 --> 00:49:36,605
Is he insane?

616
00:49:37,894 --> 00:49:42,153
He meant he's too good for that stuff, huh?

617
00:49:42,884 --> 00:49:44,424
Unbelievable.

618
00:49:45,596 --> 00:49:47,786
- Let's head out.
- Let's go.

619
00:49:47,786 --> 00:49:49,319
Good work today.

620
00:49:54,936 --> 00:49:56,936
I smell sweaty.

621
00:49:58,710 --> 00:49:59,920
Aren't you going home?

622
00:49:59,920 --> 00:50:01,653
I have work to do.

623
00:50:01,653 --> 00:50:04,723
You sat there blank all day.

624
00:50:04,723 --> 00:50:08,762
Bad students always hit
the library after exams...

625
00:50:11,088 --> 00:50:13,567
I'm studying Excel.

626
00:50:13,567 --> 00:50:17,189
Casey keeps scolding me.

627
00:50:19,180 --> 00:50:22,058
No, I didn't scold him.

628
00:50:25,397 --> 00:50:28,461
I'll teach him myself. Then we'll leave.

629
00:50:28,461 --> 00:50:31,591
What about the Sales Team dinner?

630
00:50:31,591 --> 00:50:32,816
Oh right.

631
00:50:33,494 --> 00:50:36,840
You just want to drink. Nice excuse.

632
00:50:39,901 --> 00:50:41,534
[Intern Hwang Jun Hyeon]

633
00:50:57,415 --> 00:51:01,245
Chairman Kang's master ID can access every file

634
00:51:01,245 --> 00:51:03,597
on the group server.

635
00:51:16,702 --> 00:51:17,739
[Transfer Complete]

636
00:51:19,604 --> 00:51:21,897
Time to go there.

637
00:51:25,084 --> 00:51:28,569
Not having a chairman-only elevator

638
00:51:28,569 --> 00:51:30,655
was a stroke of genius.

639
00:51:37,319 --> 00:51:39,261
And I even removed all the CCTV

640
00:51:39,261 --> 00:51:44,296
from the chairman's office, the hallway,
and the secretary's office.

641
00:51:47,781 --> 00:51:49,801
Access granted.

642
00:52:48,583 --> 00:52:49,831
- Here you go.
- Good.

643
00:52:49,831 --> 00:52:51,946
- Good work today.
- Thank you.

644
00:52:56,660 --> 00:52:59,522
- Let me pour you one.
- Thanks.

645
00:53:05,542 --> 00:53:08,589
- I'll run to the store.
- Okay.

646
00:53:14,978 --> 00:53:17,976
I'm going to the store. Need cigarettes?

647
00:53:17,976 --> 00:53:20,500
77 for you, This Minus for you,

648
00:53:20,500 --> 00:53:22,070
and Esse for you, huh?

649
00:53:22,070 --> 00:53:24,176
I'll be right back.

650
00:53:29,367 --> 00:53:31,089
Why does she...

651
00:53:32,270 --> 00:53:34,061
keep coming to our dinners?

652
00:53:34,061 --> 00:53:37,687
We already gave her
all subcontractor inventory.

653
00:53:38,320 --> 00:53:41,331
Except the ones you mentioned.

654
00:53:41,331 --> 00:53:43,768
Yujin, IB, and Hwain?

655
00:53:43,768 --> 00:53:46,092
Yes. Why leave them out?

656
00:53:46,092 --> 00:53:49,285
If she finds out, I'll never make manager.

657
00:53:49,285 --> 00:53:50,707
Just do as I say.

658
00:53:55,405 --> 00:53:58,757
[Yujin, IB, Hwain]

659
00:53:59,434 --> 00:54:01,508
What are these?

660
00:54:44,998 --> 00:54:47,215
He's good-looking.

661
00:55:42,771 --> 00:55:46,106
Skip anyone who knows too many people.

662
00:55:47,044 --> 00:55:50,710
Skip anyone who looks rich.

663
00:55:56,964 --> 00:55:58,556
A shadow.

664
00:55:58,556 --> 00:56:01,422
Money trouble all over her face.

665
00:56:04,137 --> 00:56:05,529
Excuse me.

666
00:56:06,378 --> 00:56:08,595
You work so hard.

667
00:56:08,595 --> 00:56:10,522
Nurse Song Gyeong Seon.

668
00:56:11,828 --> 00:56:14,319
Could you spare just five minutes?

669
00:56:14,319 --> 00:56:15,931
What...

670
00:56:18,172 --> 00:56:19,993
Let's talk over there.

671
00:56:28,565 --> 00:56:30,302
What is this?

672
00:56:30,302 --> 00:56:33,985
Just tell me Chairman Kang's condition.

673
00:56:33,985 --> 00:56:37,292
Don't worry. I'm not a reporter.

674
00:56:38,201 --> 00:56:40,092
What do you take me for?

675
00:56:40,092 --> 00:56:41,502
No pressure.

676
00:56:41,502 --> 00:56:43,151
You can say no.

677
00:56:45,945 --> 00:56:48,169
This won't be a one-time thing.

678
00:56:48,169 --> 00:56:52,703
Keep me updated on him,
and you'll keep getting this much.

679
00:56:52,703 --> 00:56:56,293
Someone will leak it anyway.

680
00:56:56,293 --> 00:57:00,253
Might as well get paid.

681
00:57:04,323 --> 00:57:07,944
His body is fine.

682
00:57:07,944 --> 00:57:10,750
But we don't know when he'll wake up.

683
00:57:10,750 --> 00:57:12,311
You mean brain death?

684
00:57:12,311 --> 00:57:14,461
His brain activity is fine.

685
00:57:17,986 --> 00:57:19,589
Actually...

686
00:57:19,589 --> 00:57:24,086
he had a brief cardiac arrest days ago.
He could die just like that.

687
00:57:34,772 --> 00:57:36,785
I need one more favor.

688
00:57:36,785 --> 00:57:38,750
When this man comes, give him this.

689
00:57:39,852 --> 00:57:41,964
Did Chairman Kang write this?

690
00:57:41,964 --> 00:57:44,496
He woke up briefly before the coma.

691
00:57:44,496 --> 00:57:46,653
He asked me to give it to you.

692
00:57:46,653 --> 00:57:48,623
He said not to tell anyone.

693
00:57:48,623 --> 00:57:51,029
Even Professor Min doesn't know.

694
00:58:03,140 --> 00:58:04,779
Chairman...

695
00:58:06,177 --> 00:58:08,049
[Gangwon Port Infrastructure Project]
Use this for your PT.

696
00:58:09,381 --> 00:58:11,480
You need to at least look prepared.

697
00:58:11,480 --> 00:58:13,818
Why you, of all people?

698
00:58:13,818 --> 00:58:18,538
It has to be a two-person team.
And no one else wants you.

699
00:58:20,574 --> 00:58:22,697
Be honest.

700
00:58:22,697 --> 00:58:23,788
Do you...

701
00:58:27,713 --> 00:58:29,187
like him?

702
00:58:30,440 --> 00:58:32,084
Are you kidding?

703
00:58:32,084 --> 00:58:35,670
You're here to work, not date.

704
00:58:37,970 --> 00:58:40,054
No no...

705
00:58:40,054 --> 00:58:41,893
No work ethic at all.

706
00:58:42,920 --> 00:58:45,279
To expose him,

707
00:58:45,279 --> 00:58:48,006
I need to keep him close.

708
00:58:50,955 --> 00:58:55,330
Be grateful I'm letting you in, Mr. Delulu.

709
00:58:56,716 --> 00:59:00,755
You're lucky to be teamed with me.

710
00:59:02,417 --> 00:59:04,506
"Mr. Delulu."

711
00:59:05,239 --> 00:59:08,143
Overseas smart logistics
and industrial parks...

712
00:59:08,143 --> 00:59:11,042
will combine our trading
and distribution strengths...

713
00:59:11,042 --> 00:59:14,687
to lead a Korean-style global...

714
00:59:14,687 --> 00:59:16,981
industrial park model.

715
00:59:16,981 --> 00:59:18,987
Thank you.

716
00:59:21,781 --> 00:59:24,971
Last up, Team 6, please.

717
00:59:26,057 --> 00:59:29,049
The final team. That Hwang Jun Hyeon guy.

718
00:59:29,901 --> 00:59:32,071
Do we have to see this?

719
00:59:32,071 --> 00:59:34,351
Can't we skip it?

720
00:59:34,351 --> 00:59:36,705
You should stay and watch, sir.

721
00:59:40,924 --> 00:59:41,940
When did she get here?

722
00:59:41,940 --> 00:59:44,135
You should watch this,

723
00:59:44,135 --> 00:59:45,397
CEO Kang.

724
00:59:45,397 --> 00:59:46,981
Wow.

725
00:59:51,411 --> 00:59:54,060
So, our proposal is...

726
00:59:54,060 --> 00:59:58,126
Cut ties with Yujin Networks, IB Global,
and Hwain Dynamics.

727
00:59:58,126 --> 01:00:02,723
That brings in over 30 billion won
in net profit each year.

728
01:00:09,411 --> 01:00:10,778
That's all.

729
01:00:17,483 --> 01:00:20,293
Hey, did you even read my proposal?

730
01:00:22,469 --> 01:00:23,903
Gather around.

731
01:00:24,869 --> 01:00:26,800
Don't worry.

732
01:00:26,800 --> 01:00:29,234
It worked better than your proposal.

733
01:00:33,978 --> 01:00:36,304
Except the ones you mentioned.

734
01:00:36,304 --> 01:00:38,744
Yujin, IB, and Hwain?

735
01:00:47,147 --> 01:00:49,977
Maybe he just guessed.

736
01:00:49,977 --> 01:00:53,284
Guessed those three?

737
01:00:53,284 --> 01:00:55,547
Exactly those three?

738
01:00:55,547 --> 01:00:58,168
Did you keep your people quiet?

739
01:00:58,168 --> 01:01:00,051
Nothing leaked from our side.

740
01:01:00,051 --> 01:01:01,445
I'm sure of it.

741
01:01:01,445 --> 01:01:03,576
Then how did he know?

742
01:01:03,576 --> 01:01:05,924
- Those are...
- What are they?

743
01:01:05,924 --> 01:01:09,148
Explain. We're on the same team.

744
01:01:09,148 --> 01:01:12,630
All they do is issue tax invoices.

745
01:01:12,630 --> 01:01:15,417
They take middleman cuts
between Trading affiliates.

746
01:01:15,417 --> 01:01:18,316
The company runs fine without them.

747
01:01:18,316 --> 01:01:20,649
- In other words...
- Kang Jae Seong's...

748
01:01:20,649 --> 01:01:22,032
slush fund channels?

749
01:01:22,032 --> 01:01:23,447
You...

750
01:01:23,447 --> 01:01:26,449
might become full-time thanks to me.

751
01:01:26,449 --> 01:01:28,473
How do you know that?

752
01:01:28,473 --> 01:01:30,497
Hidden offshore funds?

753
01:01:30,497 --> 01:01:33,347
CEO Kang Jae Seong has 300 billion.

754
01:01:33,347 --> 01:01:35,261
Why expose that?

755
01:01:35,261 --> 01:01:38,834
- Weren't you on Jae Seong's side?
- No.

756
01:01:38,834 --> 01:01:40,503
I'm on his side.

757
01:01:42,527 --> 01:01:44,433
Call a CEO meeting.

758
01:01:44,433 --> 01:01:46,121
Right now.

759
01:01:49,062 --> 01:01:50,979
Why did you come to Choiseong?

760
01:01:50,979 --> 01:01:54,381
Who the hell are you?

761
01:02:03,655 --> 01:02:06,037
That PT wore you out?

762
01:02:07,401 --> 01:02:09,391
You're late.

763
01:02:09,391 --> 01:02:11,352
Your sister joined Choiseong.

764
01:02:11,352 --> 01:02:12,779
What?

765
01:02:14,144 --> 01:02:16,110
You mean her?

766
01:02:16,110 --> 01:02:19,904
I called you here with a message
from Chairman Kang.

767
01:02:20,514 --> 01:02:21,898
Recently,

768
01:02:21,898 --> 01:02:25,058
he briefly regained consciousness

769
01:02:25,058 --> 01:02:27,368
and left this letter.

770
01:02:27,368 --> 01:02:30,095
Oh, he woke up?

771
01:02:30,095 --> 01:02:32,498
What does it say?

772
01:02:35,747 --> 01:02:38,190
I hereby order this.

773
01:02:38,190 --> 01:02:41,498
From this moment on, there will be no...

774
01:02:42,307 --> 01:02:43,990
bloodline succession.

775
01:02:48,138 --> 01:02:53,602
Every Choiseong employee has
the right to become chairman.

776
01:02:53,602 --> 01:02:55,533
Until I return,

777
01:02:55,533 --> 01:02:59,179
Lee Sang Jae of Strategic Planning

778
01:02:59,179 --> 01:03:02,719
will serve as acting chairman.

779
01:03:04,809 --> 01:03:06,181
Are you kidding?

780
01:03:06,181 --> 01:03:08,484
You wrote that letter, huh?

781
01:03:09,697 --> 01:03:12,103
From Korea, the U.S., and Japan.

782
01:03:12,103 --> 01:03:16,329
All three top agencies say

783
01:03:16,329 --> 01:03:20,250
it is 100% Chairman Kang's handwriting.

784
01:03:25,682 --> 01:03:28,479
We'll verify it again.

785
01:03:28,479 --> 01:03:31,125
Even if he wrote it after waking up,

786
01:03:31,125 --> 01:03:33,228
he's already been removed.

787
01:03:33,228 --> 01:03:36,417
He has no authority over succession.

788
01:03:36,417 --> 01:03:39,519
Then which of you will become chairman?

789
01:03:40,411 --> 01:03:42,734
CEO Kang Jae Seong?

790
01:03:42,734 --> 01:03:44,886
Or CEO Kang Jae Gyeong?

791
01:03:44,886 --> 01:03:47,155
Tell us if you've agreed.

792
01:03:47,155 --> 01:03:48,574
Well...

793
01:03:51,975 --> 01:03:54,365
We can't leave his seat empty for long.

794
01:03:54,365 --> 01:03:56,269
And I'm only a stand-in.

795
01:03:57,309 --> 01:03:59,256
So don't worry.

796
01:03:59,256 --> 01:04:02,387
If you work hard, you two still qualify.

797
01:04:21,311 --> 01:04:23,808
Then do I qualify too?

798
01:04:24,435 --> 01:04:26,754
To become chairman of Choiseong?

799
01:04:33,552 --> 01:04:35,761
This is only the beginning.

800
01:04:35,761 --> 01:04:39,290
Everything you enjoyed thanks to me,

801
01:04:39,290 --> 01:04:41,557
I'll take it back one by one.

802
01:04:44,105 --> 01:04:46,158
Look forward to it.

803
01:05:12,572 --> 01:05:14,305
Am I full-time now?

804
01:05:14,305 --> 01:05:15,339
For real?

805
01:05:15,339 --> 01:05:17,735
I don't know. You fix it.

806
01:05:17,735 --> 01:05:19,466
You idiots!

807
01:05:19,466 --> 01:05:21,319
Are you kidding me?

808
01:05:21,319 --> 01:05:23,343
We back the CEO.

809
01:05:23,343 --> 01:05:24,615
That's our trap.

810
01:05:24,615 --> 01:05:25,647
Nice.

811
01:05:25,647 --> 01:05:28,133
I'm about to die here.

812
01:05:28,133 --> 01:05:29,637
Find it. Now!

813
01:05:29,637 --> 01:05:32,277
You'll pit Trading against Chemicals?

814
01:05:32,277 --> 01:05:33,327
Scout me.

815
01:05:33,327 --> 01:05:35,351
Whose spy are you?

816
01:05:35,351 --> 01:05:37,961
Come on, this is too much!

817
01:05:37,961 --> 01:05:39,321
Stay sharp.

818
01:05:39,321 --> 01:05:41,374
Give up everything and die...

819
01:05:42,791 --> 01:05:45,691
or trust me once.
